        class="reveal-on-scroll mt-8 font-[family-name:var(--font-body)] text-[15px] leading-[1.85] text-charcoal/70"
      >
        A living archive of ethnobotanical wisdom accumulated across millennia by indigenous
        cultures of Central America and the Caribbean — preserved through wildcrafted, shade-dried
        plants sourced directly from the landscapes where they have always grown.
      </p>
      <p
        class="reveal-on-scroll mt-4 font-[family-name:var(--font-body)] text-[15px] leading-[1.85] text-charcoal/70"
      >
        Honduras sits at a unique ecological crossroads. Cloud forests, tropical lowlands, river
        corridors, and coastal ecosystems converge here to create extraordinary botanical diversity.
        The plants in this collection have never been treated as commodities — they are integral to
        cultural identity, daily life, and ancestral practice.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {
    /* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
      ORIGIN — OriginChapter asymmetric with green accent
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */
  }
